---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';
import headshot from '../assets/headshot_halftone_green.png';
---
<Default>
  <div class="wrap">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <header class="profile-header">
      <Image
        src={headshot}
        alt="Morgan Stone"
        width={144}
        height={144}
        class="avatar"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        format="avif"
      />
      <p class="eyebrow">Morgan Stone<br>Director of Software Engineering</p>
    </header>

    <h1 class="headline">
      I translate business goals into <strong>high-velocity technical execution</strong> across a 32-person global org.
    </h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      Architecture &times; P&amp;L. Came up through marketing and design, went deep on full-stack and systems engineering - which means I frame architecture decisions in business terms rather than purely technical ones. Ten years scaling teams and platforms through three acquisitions.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-group">
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/morganstone/" class="cta-btn cta-btn--primary" onclick="captureOutboundLink('https://www.linkedin.com/in/morganstone/')">
        LinkedIn
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/mstone6769" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost" onclick="captureOutboundLink('https://github.com/mstone6769')">
        GitHub
      </a>
      <a href="/bbq-links" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost">
        BBQ Links
      </a>
    </div>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Impact stats -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:28px">Selected impact</p>
    <div class="stats">
      <div>
        <p class="stat-value">$14.5M</p>
        <p class="stat-label">revenue protected<br>SOC 2 Type 1 &amp; 2</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="stat-value">22.4<span style="font-size:0.55em;letter-spacing:0">/wk</span></p>
        <p class="stat-label">releases at elite DORA<br>26.4-hr median lead time</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="stat-value">$300K<span style="font-size:0.55em">+</span></p>
        <p class="stat-label">FinOps savings<br>AWS, tooling, version control</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="stat-value">$1M</p>
        <p class="stat-label">TSA eliminated<br>5-person op &rarr; 1 strategic hire</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Selected wins -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:28px">Selected wins</p>
    <div class="wins">

      <article class="win-card">
        <p class="win-eyebrow">Compliance</p>
        <p class="win-metric">$14.5M</p>
        <h2 class="win-title">Protected a health-system revenue stream through SOC 2</h2>
        <p class="win-body">
          Directed the SOC 2 Type 1 and Type 2 effort, then maintained that posture across annual audit cycles. Ran compliance and delivery in parallel - core-site accessibility held at 97% throughout.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="win-card">
        <p class="win-eyebrow">Partnership</p>
        <p class="win-metric">164 days</p>
        <h2 class="win-title">Zocdoc scheduling integration, 107K+ providers</h2>
        <p class="win-body">
          Delivered a complex scheduling partnership end-to-end in under six months, expanding provider search to 107,000+ doctors. The integration was covered in Newsweek.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="win-card">
        <p class="win-eyebrow">Delivery</p>
        <p class="win-metric">~44&times;</p>
        <h2 class="win-title">Elite DORA from a coupled .NET monolith</h2>
        <p class="win-body">
          Deprecated a bi-weekly release train by migrating the highest-traffic pages to Kubernetes-orchestrated Node.js and GraphQL. Took deployment frequency from 0.5 to 22.4 releases/week. DevEx score of 70.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="win-card win-card--wide">
        <p class="win-eyebrow">FinOps</p>
        <p class="win-metric">$300K<span style="font-size:0.6em">+</span></p>
        <h2 class="win-title">Three levers of infrastructure savings</h2>
        <p class="win-body">AWS cost optimization, a technology vendor consolidation, and folding 600+ repos onto a single version-control platform - each attack surface identified and closed across separate initiative cycles.</p>
        <svg
          class="finops-bar"
          viewBox="0 0 1000 24"
          preserveAspectRatio="none"
          role="img"
          aria-label="FinOps savings breakdown: AWS cost 170K (55%), QA infrastructure 94K (30%), version control consolidation 45K (15%)"
        >
          <defs>
            <clipPath id="bar-clip">
              <rect width="1000" height="24" rx="4" ry="4" />
            </clipPath>
          </defs>
          <g clip-path="url(#bar-clip)">
            <rect x="0"   width="550" height="24" fill="#a1be63" />
            <rect x="550" width="304" height="24" fill="#c2d790" />
            <rect x="854" width="146" height="24" fill="#7f9a48" />
          </g>
        </svg>
        <ul class="finops-legend">
          <li><span class="legend-swatch" style="background:#a1be63" aria-hidden="true"></span>AWS cost &middot; $170K</li>
          <li><span class="legend-swatch" style="background:#c2d790" aria-hidden="true"></span>QA infra &middot; $94K</li>
          <li><span class="legend-swatch" style="background:#7f9a48" aria-hidden="true"></span>600+ repos &middot; $45K</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

    </div>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Technical range -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:28px">Technical range</p>
    <div class="tech-range">
      <div>
        <p class="tech-group-label">Languages</p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tech-tag">TypeScript</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">JavaScript</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Node.js</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="tech-group-label">Frontend / API</p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tech-tag">Angular</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">React</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">GraphQL</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">REST</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="tech-group-label">Data</p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tech-tag">PostgreSQL</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Elasticsearch</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Redis</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Snowflake</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="tech-group-label">Platform</p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tech-tag">AWS</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Kubernetes</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">CI/CD</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">Feature Flags</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="tech-group-label">Practices</p>
        <div class="tech-tags">
          <span class="tech-tag">DORA</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">TDD</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">SOC 2 / HITRUST</span>
          <span class="tech-tag">WCAG</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Career -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:28px">Career</p>
    <ol class="career-list" reversed>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">Jul 2023 &ndash; Present</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">Director of Software Engineering</p>
          <p class="career-company">RVO Health</p>
          <p class="career-body">Lead a 32-person global org across 6 core teams and 3 engineering managers. Scope covers platform architecture, compliance, strategic partnerships, and FinOps. Held delivery cadence and organizational trust through two major restructuring cycles.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">Jun 2022 &ndash; Jul 2023</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">Software Engineering Manager</p>
          <p class="career-company">RVO Health</p>
          <p class="career-body">Strategic insourcing, TSA elimination, and succession planning ahead of a Director promotion. Mentored a senior engineer into an engineering manager role.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">Aug 2021 &ndash; Jun 2022</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">Software Engineering Manager</p>
          <p class="career-company">Red Ventures</p>
          <p class="career-body">Led the first phase of platform modernization - migrating Healthgrades' highest-traffic pages off legacy .NET to Kubernetes-orchestrated Node.js and GraphQL, serving 60% of site traffic and 420K+ daily users.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">Aug 2018 &ndash; Aug 2021</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">Software Engineering Manager</p>
          <p class="career-company">Influence Health / Healthgrades</p>
          <p class="career-body">Prototyped a greenfield CDP in five days to secure executive approval post-acquisition, then built it out on Elasticsearch under HITRUST. Merged disparate engineering teams and moved them from high-risk quarterly deployments to reliable sprint-based releases.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">May 2014 &ndash; Aug 2018</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">UI/UX Architect</p>
          <p class="career-company">Influence Health / Medseek</p>
          <p class="career-body">Architected platform-wide design systems across enterprise healthcare SaaS, drove the flagship patient portal to WCAG Level A, and established the foundational CI/CD pipelines for front-end delivery.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="career-item">
        <div class="career-dates">2006 &ndash; 2014</div>
        <div>
          <p class="career-role">Director of Design &amp; Art Director</p>
          <p class="career-company">Zeekee Interactive</p>
          <p class="career-body">Started part-time through college, went full-time in 2010. Wore multiple hats across design, front-end development, and client strategy - including building an internal app for design approvals. The marketing-and-design foundation that informs how I frame engineering decisions today.</p>
        </div>
      </li>

    </ol>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Speaking & teaching -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:28px">Speaking &amp; teaching</p>
    <ul class="speaking-list">
      <li>Credentialed instructor, Interactive Design - UAB (2014 &ndash; 2018)</li>
      <li>React to Angular and Back Again - Birmingham JS Meetup, 2021</li>
      <li>Rapid Prototyping with Angular CLI - Women Who Code Birmingham, 2018</li>
      <li>Optimizing Angular Performance - Birmingham JS Meetup, 2016</li>
      <li>Foundation for Apps - Birmingham JS Meetup, 2015</li>
      <li>Sass: Get Spunky Writing CSS - AIGA Birmingham, 2014</li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="rule" aria-hidden="true">

    <!-- Connect -->
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:20px">Connect</p>
    <p class="connect-body">Open to conversations about engineering leadership, platform strategy, and the occasional brisket. LinkedIn is the best way in.</p>
    <div class="cta-group">
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/morganstone/" class="cta-btn cta-btn--primary" onclick="captureOutboundLink('https://www.linkedin.com/in/morganstone/')">
        LinkedIn
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/mstone6769" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost" onclick="captureOutboundLink('https://github.com/mstone6769')">
        GitHub
      </a>
      <a href="/bbq-links" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost">
        BBQ Links
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Default>
